            {
               "text": "### Images from Research Gate\n\nThese images are copyright for Research Gate and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 1</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"img9\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img9', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Representation of baboon bone adorned with markings. This image, credited to Enrique Silván Pobes, is featured in the scholarly work of Francisco A. Gonzáles Redondo et al.<br />The original is available in ResearchNet (<htcite0>), and its inclusion here is made possible by the authorization of Doctor Francisco A. Gonzales Redondo.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Beyond fingers (First Steps (Volume 1))</li><li>Understanding Texts: The Writing System - More than just a tool for daily use, the writing system is a milestone that allows us to divide human history into prehistory and recorded events. (<htcite2>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Drawing to count - Exploring how indigenous peoples developed methods for counting. (<htcite3>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Translation game (Part I)` - In this game, we offer the opportunity to translate numbers from different cultures. (<htcite4>)</li><li>Physics: Together we are strong - In this text, we see how the four operations, when combined, open the doors to so much knowledge (<htcite5>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
